<subSubSection id="9D79262BD344A1EED1157402A7B5C467" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="described species and range">
<paragraph id="4602D35BAD19AC3FF7CCED3D766B3279" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Described species and range.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38318BF6CDAB3BDABBF0458995C0409B" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Four species from New Guinea, the Philippines, Cambodia (B. Gueorguiev in litt.), and central Africa.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AF599352EA793E3022D56FC507CA3343" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="description">
<paragraph id="3EF534232ECCC427A9754E88CE95E091" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Adult characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1A467ECEB67F02D86CD88D33DDAF2EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Small sized beetles (3.5-5.0 mm). These beetles are moderately convex, shiny, brown and the elytra somewhat or significantly iridescent. In general form they are similar to some small species of 
<taxonomicName id="6B91446B10F9628222141CA0F39A8DA4" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lecanomerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lecanomerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="471DC5BE1814422B94DE794976C0E8F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Lecanomerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1850 or larger 
<taxonomicName id="75C1667BA064CB3BCB347CC19467478B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CE83B2B5A2EBBF13B8898298BF8D3022" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1821. Recognizable from other, similar looking abacetine genera by the combination of deep post-ocular sulcus, smooth elytral margins; and lack of elytral discal setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="854FE9DBB93F14259B703899683E367C" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="life history notes">
<paragraph id="A104BD6CBB48C9B7C5AFD1063EE35DFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Life history notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32ED2E4BBB643DF44A291725FB608E75" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Wet, shady areas near water (
<bibRefCitation id="0012FE966B5AAF322F6CC4FA00C14875" author="Darlington, PJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="321 - 564" refId="B33" refString="Darlington, PJ, 1962. The Carabid beetles of New Guinea Part I. Cicindelinae, Carabinae, Harpalinae through Pterostichini. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College 126: 321 - 564" title="The Carabid beetles of New Guinea Part I. Cicindelinae, Carabinae, Harpalinae through Pterostichini." volume="126" year="1962">Darlington 1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3F0986449B5A789B5632B44635A8AB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B38F2C47B04DD2736B7331EF635CBAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7CD7B68B101209C73DBB821BB726A543" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Darlington described 
<taxonomicName id="44C3C61C86F89DD5246E516715878F61" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9ED0C6086DF0C968D190AC9A7A7BCC5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being &quot;a minute 
<taxonomicName id="D3022F3DD230421D9A1CA994668A3432" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Loxandrus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CAAC10FF188292EDC36A917C3F0B5EC8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Loxandrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; with a few significant differences, he also discusses the possibility that they are related to 
<taxonomicName id="272543FDBBC0C39DDBE088268C35A3F9" authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Melanchrous" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanchrous" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EC37718A35EC8ED010D56912DAA02BE8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Melanchrous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Andrewes or 
<taxonomicName id="9C5751817948EC4536BBCB55491F0F66" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holconotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holconotus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DE7943854E3E6EA5DD70AE2A6AFABA6C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Holconotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schmidt-Goebel, 1846 (= 
<taxonomicName id="382ADEE5F70612D9FF6B8DCBDA3F09DD" authority="Maindron, 1906" authorityName="Maindron" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Fouquetius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fouquetius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A9280B5D28F74253B047A72563D20035" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Fouquetius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Maindron, 1906), with the latter relationship having more character support. 
<taxonomicName id="FE4AF3CE32F8525A1E0A33BD4966D6D0" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0F0807CBD9FB4CD4A8EA1988072E97EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has sinuate metacoxal sulci that end in the middle of the coxa, sharply impressed and divergent frontal impressions, symmetrically expanded male protarsi, a moderately transverse mentum, and lacks the puncture on interval 3 of the elytral disc. All of these characteristic are also found in 
<taxonomicName id="2EB9DF9C0ADC38CFDC01561BB48E6EE8" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holconotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holconotus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="50C9F95E867B18DB22B9FD267C9BAA70" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Holconotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but also in many other 
<taxonomicName id="C9332C24331CE5853195F20BF5D765C0" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holconotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Abacetina">Abacetina</taxonomicName>
taxa. 
<taxonomicName id="87A4EB0406C33033A75ACBA2CDD01CD9" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="11C12151251598B4494B223FF1552AAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E61D178F9FC8061D6DCD0AAEA4FA2499" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holconotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holconotus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DCFDB939C873F13E661CDE8D276CDC03" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Holconotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species share the presence of a sharply impressed sulcus on the non-ommatidia portion of the ocular orbit just behind the eye, a character not found in any other 
<taxonomicName id="33E12212E6BA03444DCD34480D2383C7" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1873" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="tribe" tribe="Abacetini">Abacetini</taxonomicName>
species and likely a synapomorphy for these two genera. 
<taxonomicName id="874CC3B34F8FB72FBEB981A7B4B1E3C5" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="11BE0B8E075E9100A8E338E099D3E646" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the serrulations near the humeri on the elytral marginal bead that are found in 
<taxonomicName id="A41DCC3B4664D3E6F4FB02D2321C0765" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Holconotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holconotus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A8F4A67936FDC0E7B0F7644C25737E1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Holconotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="547717DC67BE606E511C479929E0024E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.906.48255" author="Will, KW" journalOrPublisher="Zookeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="131 - 140" refId="B125" refString="Will, KW, 2020a. Review and new species of Tiferonia Darlington, 1962 (Carabidae, Abacetini). Zookeys 906: 131 - 140, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.906.48255" title="Review and new species of Tiferonia Darlington, 1962 (Carabidae, Abacetini)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.906.48255" volume="906" year="2020 a">Will 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="F8D11266076DAD2AE13E27D5C5F60097" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96C5FC5EE0396463AA31E0D52363A9E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have the asymmetrically inserted second antennomeres as is found in 
<taxonomicName id="7D6DC1E2FB3EEC3F77E400F0174E1D35" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Abacetus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abacetus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3AD75751618F061543C5355FC394FF63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abacetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and many other putatively related genera. Given its character state combination, 
<taxonomicName id="5A528F801379C283BCEA5BDF3A2635EA" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tiferonia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="828938EFC6DD3836363160B824877F41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tiferonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely in a grade of 
<taxonomicName id="FA7607E07458C99F5FD2B6A4E1736685" authorityName="Darlington" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tiferonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Abacetina">Abacetina</taxonomicName>
taxa, near genera like 
<taxonomicName id="DE28E4D2F3F7BFDBB23E2619EA987B93" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Metabacetus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metabacetus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="208CB175FB70A9C6898B49F86FD29A27" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Metabacetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3A255B12AAEC8768ED3916FFF09F24AA" authorityName="Sloane" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Cosmodiscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cosmodiscus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C0FAC9465AC0FD31E10CC6AB110A599B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Cosmodiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
